            <title>[MAHOUT-1223] Point skipped in StreamingKMeans when iterating through centroids from a reducer</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MAHOUT-1223</link>
                <project id="12310751" key="MAHOUT">Mahout</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When calling StreamingKMeans in the reducer (to collapse the number of clusters to they can fit into memory), the clustering is done on the Hadoop reducer iterable.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Currently, the first Centroid is added directly as a special case and then is skipped when iterating through the main loop.&lt;br/&gt;
However, Hadoop reducer iterables cannot be rewound therefore causing SKM to skip one point.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
