&lt;p&gt;When calling StreamingKMeans in the reducer (to collapse the number of clusters&lt;br/&gt;
to they can fit into memory), the clustering is done on the Hadoop reducer&lt;br/&gt;
iterable.&lt;br/&gt;
Currently, the first Centroid is added directly as a special case and then is&lt;br/&gt;
skipped when iterating through the main loop.&lt;br/&gt;
However, Hadoop reducer iterables cannot be rewound therefore causing SKM to&lt;br/&gt;
skip one point. (Revision 1484747)&lt;/p&gt;

